{"word":"ἁλίζω","slug":"ἁλίζω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἁλίζω1</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἁλής'><el>ἁλής</el></a>\n<p/><i>to gather together, to muster</i>, military forces, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to meet together, assemble</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/> <hr/> <el><b>ἁλίζω2</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><el>ἅλς</el>\n<p/><i>to salt</i>, and <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be salted</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristotle'>Arist.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:New Testament'>NTest.</a></b><p/>"}]}